### Rewrite of Lead

I've noticed the article's lead summary both contains a lot of redundant information and some inaccuracies

1. The fact thermodynamics are not relevant and electromagnetism isn't something a computer engineer will really ever have to deal with outside of niche embedded systems.

2. When discussing the scope of computer engineering, it mentions the same things multiple times and defines the scope differently on two occasions.

3. It has a weird mention of robotics

4. Fails to clarify that computer engineering is mostly about digital and not analog electronics

5. There's no widely agreed upon definition and as a result there isn't too much degree standardization. This is more of an education section comment, but it's still worth mentioning to some extent in my opinion

